file=AI & Agents/scout/operational/commands/scout-commands.md · tb=\| Trigger phrases \| Skill \| Shortcut \| · tb=\|---\|---\|---\| · tb=\| "what's new in tools", "scan the ecosystem", "weekly sweep", "find us an X" \| ecosystem-scanning \| /scan \| · tb=\| "evaluate this tool", "new mcp", "trial this", "should we use", "trial expired" \| tool-evaluation-intake \| /evaluate \| · tb=\| "did we already look at", "why was X rejected", "watch list", "re-open" \| adopt-reject-registry \| /verdicts \| · tb=\| "is there a real skill for", "marketplace search", "search by purpose", "pending candidates" \| marketplace-skill-scouting \| /skillscout \| · p:Precedence=1. Repeat candidates: adopt-reject-registry check FIRST, always — before any scan shortlist or intake.\n2. Skill-shaped finds → marketplace-skill-scouting; tool-shaped → tool-evaluation-intake; technique-shaped → hand to forge.\n3. An expiring trial outranks new scans (verdicts before discovery).\n